message: If you use this work, please cite it using the metadata below.
type: dataset
title: Network Performance Measurement Experiment with Client, Server, and Proxy Components
abstract: This dataset documents a network performance measurement experiment involving
  client, server, and proxy components deployed across multiple nodes. The methodology
  involved configuring network interfaces and queuing disciplines to simulate controlled
  network conditions, followed by the execution of client and server applications
  under varying configurations. Energy consumption data was captured during these
  runs, alongside packet capture for proxy evaluation. The dataset includes scripts
  used for environment setup, dependency installation, topology configuration, workload
  generation, visualization, and result archival.
